==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: funeral home
<hw>fu"ner*al home`</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>An establishment, usually
commercial, where the bodies of dead persons are prepared for viewing
before burial or cremation; called also <altname>funeral
parlor</altname>, <altname>mortuary</altname>, <altname>funeral
chapel</altname> and informally, <altname>undertaker's</altname>. The
body may or may not be preserved by embalming before viewing or burial,
and in some cases the body is not exposed for viewing, though present in
a casket. Often, some form of memorial service is held for the deceased
at the funeral home, where friends and relatives may come to pay their
respects to the dead, and express condolence to the family. The work of
preparation of the body and many other arrangements related to the
funeral and burial are carried out by an undertaker or mortician who
manages the <ex>funeral home</ex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>funeral parlor</ent>⟦br⟧
